OL,3,CBMA backs family suing regulator over
OL,4,Cthe role of NHS physician associates
OL,6,F"Physician associates and anaesthesia
OL,7,Fassociates are not doctors, cannot
OL,8,Freplace them, and should never be used
OL,9,Fto fill gaps in doctors' rotas. When
OL,10,Fwe begin regulating PAs and AAs later
OL,11,Fthis year, we will expect them to be
OL,12,Fsupervised by a doctor and to practise
OL,13,Fwithin their competence. In regulating
OL,14,FPAs and AAs, we will be clear that
OL,15,Fpeople in these roles will have a
OL,16,Fresponsibility to communicate who they
OL,17,Fare, and their role in the team.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/17
